# MackesWorkstation per-user control plane (mackesd serve).
#
# SHIPPED DISABLED for now (Bug 6, 2026-06-06). The unit is installed and ready,
# but `mackesd serve` currently spawns the FULL worker set even as a per-user
# daemon — including fabric workers that can never succeed off a per-user/
# non-enrolled box (nebula_https_listener binds privileged :443 + needs a
# lighthouse cert; fs-sync exits 1). They respawn ~4x/sec (the OnFailure backoff
# does not actually quarantine), so auto-enabling would ship a crash-loop.
#
# Flip this to `enable mackesd.service` once serve gains a per-user worker subset
# (or the fabric workers are prereq-gated + the backoff capped). Until then an
# operator can start it manually with `systemctl --user enable --now mackesd`.
disable mackesd.service
